IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE INTELLECTUAL, MORAL & RELIGIOUS GROWTH OF PEOPLE IN THE UNIVERSITY OF WISCONSIN COMMUNITY IN WAYS CONSISTENT WITH THE PRINCIPALS & PURPOSES OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (USA).
IRS990.MissionDesc: PRES HOUSE SEEKS TO BE A SPIRITUAL HOME AT THE HEART OF THE UNIVERSITY OF WISCONSIN-MADISON CAMPUS. IN KEEPING WITH THE TEACHINGS OF JESUS CHRIST AND THE CHRISTIAN TRADITION OF HOSPITALITY, PRES HOUSE IS DEDICATED TO PROVIDING A RELIGIOUS CENTER AND PURPOSEFUL HOUSING TO SUPPORT THE SPIRITUAL, EMOTIONAL, AND INTELLECTUAL GROWTH OF RESIDENTS AND MEMBERS OF THE UW-MADISON CAMPUS COMMUNITY. PRES HOUSE IS A MINISTRY OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH, U.S.A. AND WELCOMES INDIVIDUALS OF EVERY PERSPECTIVE AND BACKGROUND.
IRS990.Desc: RESIDENCE COMMUNITY THE FOUNDATION PROVIDES A RELIGIOUS CENTER AND HIGH-QUALITY STUDENT HOUSING TO PROMOTE THE SPIRITUAL, EMOTIONAL, AND INTELLECTUAL GROWTH OF THE RESIDENTS AND MEMBERS OF THE CAMPUS COMMUNITY. TO ACCOMPLISH THIS GOAL, THE FOUNDATION PROVIDES DISCUSSION GROUPS, STUDY SPACES, MEALS, SERVICE OPPORTUNITIES, AND OTHER EVENTS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: CHURCH MINISTRY - AS A MINISTRY OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH, U.S.A., PRES HOUSE PROVIDES WORSHIP SERVICES AND OTHER SERVICES TO MEET THE SPIRITUAL NEEDS OF THE CAMPUS COMMUNITY.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION MAINTAINS A CLOSE AND CONTINUOUS WORKING RELATIONSHIP WITH THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A.) BECAUSE IT IS AN OUTREACH MISSION OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A.) AND AS SUCH DRAWS ON THE RICH DEEP WELL OF CONFESSIONAL STATEMENTS OF THE LARGER CHURCH. BY REASON OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A.) MEMBERS ELECTING OR CONSTITUTING ONE OR MORE OF THE PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION DIRECTORS, THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A.) HAS A SIGNIFICANT VOICE IN THE PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION'S INVESTMENT POLICIES AND IN DIRECTING USE OF PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION'S INCOME AND ASSETS.

THE PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION IS AN OUTREACH MISSION OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A) AND THEREFORE ITS ACTIVITIES ARE DIRECTLY FURTHERING THE EXEMPT PURPOSE OF THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A).

THE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH (U.S.A) ENGAGES IN MANY OF THE ACTIVITIES THAT THE PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION ENGAGES IN AND WOULD CONTINUE TO ENGAGE IN THOSE ACTIVITIES BUT FOR THE PRESBYTERIAN STUDENT CENTER FOUNDATION'S INVOLVEMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FOUNDATION'S ENDOWMENT CONSISTS OF TWO DONOR-RESTRICTED FUNDS: THE VERHULST AND MILLOT FUNDS. THESE FUNDS WERE ESTABLISHED TO PROVIDE LOANS AND EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES FOR STUDENTS.
INDIVIDUALS SUBMIT APPLICATIONS TO RECEIVE SCHOLARSHIPS. A STAFF MEMBER MANAGES THE SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM TO ENSURE RULES ARE FOLLOWED BY THE RECIPIENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PREPARED FORM 990 IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNUALLY ALL DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS COMPLETE AND SIGN A STATEMENT THAT PROVIDES INFORMATION REGARDING THEIR INTERESTS AND THOSE OF THEIR FAMILY MEMBERS THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS. THE MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY MAKE DETERMINATIONS OF WHETHER A CONFLICT EXISTS AND REVIEW ACTUAL CONFLICTS. ANY PERSON WITH A CONFLICT IS PROHIBITED FROM PARTICIPATING IN THE GOVERNING BODY'S DELIBERATIONS AND DECISIONS IN THE TRANSACTION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: UPON HIRING THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE, WHICH IS COMPRISED OF INDEPENDENT MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY, REVIEWS DATA PUBLISHED BY THE UNITED WAY ON COMPENSATION PAID BY NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS IN DANE COUNTY FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS. THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE ALSO REVIEWS NATIONAL AND REGIONAL DENOMINATIONAL DATA ON COMPENSATION PAID BY COMPARABLE ORGANIZATIONS. THIS DATA IS USED TO DETERMINE A COMPENSATION RANGE THAT IS THEN REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE ENTIRE GOVERNING BODY. ANNUALLY, THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE CONDUCTS A PERFORMANCE REVIEW AND LOOKS AT THE CONSUMER PRICE INDEX TO GAUGE INFLATION. THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE RECOMMENDS A COMPENSATION LEVEL FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR TO THE GOVERNING BODY FOR APPROVAL BASED ON THE CONSUMER PRICE INDEX, JOB PERFORMANCE, AND/OR CHANGES IN JOB RESPONSIBILITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
